# 诗云 / Poetry Cloud — build-time environment (all optional; copy to .env.local to use)
#
# The app is static by default. The server touchpoints are feedback collection and 认领 (claims).
# Vite inlines VITE_* vars into the client bundle at build time, so these values are PUBLIC.
#
# ── feedback collection (self-hosted; see docs/DEPLOY.md §5 + deploy/feedback-server.mjs) ──
# Same-origin relative path once nginx proxies /api/feedback to the collector. Leave unset (or
# blank) to keep the build 100% static: feedback then lives only in the visitor's localStorage
# (owner reads it on-device via the hidden 5-taps-on-logo gesture).
# When set, each submitted message is ALSO POSTed as JSON: {message}. The server creates receivedAt.
# VITE_FEEDBACK_ENDPOINT="/api/feedback"
#
# ── 认领 claim collector (self-hosted; see docs/DEPLOY.md §7 + deploy/claim-server.mjs) ──
# The ONLY thing the static client can't do: hand out a GLOBAL 认领编号 (claim number, from 1, shared
# across ALL users). Same-origin relative path once nginx proxies /api/claim to the collector. Leave
# unset to keep claims local-only (the poem still becomes a meteor, but its 认领编号 stays "待联网确认").
# POST /api/claim has no body → {no,ts}; GET /api/claim/feed → public [{no,ts}] meteor events.
# Poem text, previews and reversible indexes remain local-only. MAX_CLAIMS hard-caps at 1,000,000.
# VITE_CLAIM_ENDPOINT="/api/claim"
#
# ── share-preview absolute origin (og:image for Facebook/X scrapers; see index.html) ──
# Set to the deployed site origin before the production build; unset → root-relative /og.jpg
# (fine for Telegram/most CN apps, degraded for FB/X).
# VITE_SITE_ORIGIN="https://shiyun.example.com"
#
# ── data shard base (heavy poems/lines/search; see docs/DEPLOY.md §1.1 + §2.1) ──
# Where load.ts fetches the data shards from. Unset → same-origin "/data" (default; 100% static).
# Set to an absolute CDN/object-storage origin to offload egress, OR to a versioned same-origin path
# (e.g. "/data/v2") paired with the nginx immutable-cache location so byte-frozen shards cache forever.
# Trailing slashes are stripped. Bump the suffix on every data version change → old caches die naturally.
# VITE_DATA_BASE="/data/v2"
